The paper deals with the approximability of various optimization problems, which is a central topic in computational complexity theory. The focus on the trade-off between running time and approximation ratio suggests that the paper belongs to cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The problems studied, such as Max Minimal Vertex Cover and Min ATSP, involve graphs and combinatorial structures, indicating that the paper could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The mention of approximation ratios and the ETH (Exponential Time Hypothesis) suggest that the paper could also belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
